# Sub-repo manifest

Index of registered sub-repos in this company's stack. Authoritative
— the orchestrator consults this file to know what to query, what to
write notices into, and which depth file to read for each.

Update via `/register` or by editing this file directly.

> **The index, not the depth.** Each entry below is metadata only.
> Per-sub-repo accumulated state lives at
> [`state/sub-repos/<name>.md`](../../state/sub-repos/) — that's
> where current branch, HEAD, advertisement, and references to all
> orchestrator artifacts touching the repo live.
>
> **Registration discipline.** See
> [`.claude/sub-project-registration.md`](../../.claude/sub-project-registration.md)
> for how `/register` (per-repo, deliberate — first-time company
> setup) and `bin/setup` (bulk, automatic — collaborator onboarding)
> work together. The orchestrator manages its own checkouts under
> `repos/` — it does not reference external clones on the user's
> machine.

## Layout

Sub-repos clone into the orchestrator's own workspace at a fixed
convention path:

```
{{COMPANY_NAME}}-orchestrator/      cloned from <org>/<company>-orchestrator
├── .git/                            the orchestrator's repo
├── .claude/                         skills, rules, foundation.json
├── decisions/, state/, ...          the brain
├── bin/setup                        clones all sub-repos for new collaborators
└── repos/                           GITIGNORED — sub-repos clone here
    ├── api/                         (its own .git, working copy)
    ├── ios/
    ├── web/
    └── devops/
```

`repos/` is gitignored. Each sub-repo retains its own `.git` and
behaves normally inside. The path is **convention, not config** —
always `<orchestrator-root>/repos/<name>/`, never stored, never
varies per machine. Existing checkouts elsewhere on the user's
machine are not referenced — the orchestrator manages its own copies.

## Format

```
## <name>
- **Role:** api | ios | web | devops | other
- **Git remote:** <url>
- **Default branch:** main
- **Kit-enabled:** true | false | unknown
- **Registered:** YYYY-MM-DD
- **Last synced HEAD:** <sha or "never">
- **Last synced at:** YYYY-MM-DD or "never"
- **State file:** [state/sub-repos/<name>.md](state/sub-repos/<name>.md)
- **Notes:** <one-line — anything that affects how state is queried>
```

**Kit-enabled detection:** `true` if `repos/<name>/.claude/foundation.json`
exists with `kit.repo` containing `claude-kit`. `false` if it doesn't.
`unknown` only during the moment between registration and the first
`/sync-check`. On machines without local checkouts (e.g. mobile),
detection happens via `gh api` against the `git_remote`.

